            },
            "answer_text": "Yes, your phone will heat up a small amount quicker. Anything covering a phone will insulate it somewhat and prevent heat from escaping. It will also prevent air circulation from moving heat away from the phone. Generally speaking this is a small enough amount that it won't be a problem. It could, possibly, cause trouble if it's prone to heating or is being used heavily. (As noted in other answers to this question.) The only time I've seen heating problems is related to overcharging or a bad battery. I wouldn't worry about a case because they are designed to be used on phones and surely the designers would think of that. (Yes they would.) ",
