            "answer_text": "Obviously Yes!! Phone cases won\u2019t let heat dissipation faster. But the level of heating depends on the type of material of which the case is made of. If the case is heat conductive like aluminium mixed cases, it dissipates heat faster due to heat dissipation all over the case body and let your smartphone to cool down rapidly, but if the case is made of normal plastic then its gonna make your smartphone brittle in long run as the heat is trapped inside and your smartphone temp keeps increasing(heat might not be felt by the user in this case ). This is also one of the reason of trending of metal body smartphones now a days. So choose wisely or Go Caseless. :P;P ",
